message.content: The paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) as it deals with the development and release of a collection of non-factoid questions and relevance judgments for information retrieval systems. Other likely sub-categories could include "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as the paper involves natural language processing, "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of neural IR models, "cs.DL" (Machine Learning) as deep learning techniques are used, "cs.HC" (Human-Computer Interaction) as the questions were asked by real users in a community question answering service.
